dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from HDX. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following was found and fixed by ITOS: 1. Created and populated reference name field 2. Special characters in Admin2 names were corrupted, causing them to appear as random letters, numbers or blank spaces, sometimes truncating the name. This has been fixed by replacing Admin2 names with ones from Excel sheet "mex_popp_govemex_administrative_hierarchy.xlsx" 3. Admin1 names have been converted from ALL CAPS to Proper Case and special characters have been restored 4. Found and fixed 923 multipart sliver errors 5. Found and fixed 29 gap errors and 31 overlap errors 6. Found and fixed 4 nesting errors between Admin1 and 2 7. Muni_2012gw.shp was used to update layer with new unit "Bacalar". Unit has been given p-code "MX23010", provided by UNOCHA
